During an audit I came across an issue in flower 0.9.1 that allows me to inject HTML into the /tasks webpage with a specially crafted set of parameters to a task in celery. 

In this particular case the following adjustment should fix the issue in flower.js:
```
            }, {
                targets: 3,
                data: 'args',
                visible: isColumnVisible('args'),
                render: $.fn.dataTable.render.text() /* FIX : prevent args from being rendered as HTML */
            }, {
```
You should probably evaluate if other fields such as "kwargs" and "results" are vulnerable as well.

Hi,
require-instance statement is supported for leafref only in yang 1.1 (RFC 7950), but pyang successfully validates a yang-version 1 model which has a leaf like the below

```
yang-version "1";

...
leaf refleaf {
 type string;
}

leaf a {
  type leafref {
    path "/refleaf";
    require-instance true;
  }
}
```

Is this per design?

