First: This app is a huge help. Thanks. 

My question: I'm trying to work with custom_facts as referenced here https://github.com/fboender/ansible-cmdb#custom-facts, but I'm not sure I'm trying to work with it in the way it was designed. 

I can place JSON into an 'out_custom' folder for processing as described, but this seems of limited value since the point of Ansible setup is to get updated facts for each host without having to hardcode JSON. 

Is there a way for cmdb to process the custom facts feature which is built into ansible?  Dynamically generated by ansible using the /etc/ansible/facts.d folder on hosts? 

I would like to use the facts.d functionality to obtain custom facts from scripts on the hosts which output JSON dynamically - not from static JSON. 

In the CMDB documentation, it stated that custom_facts must be in the 'custom_facts' key. OK. Is there a way to modify that so the cmdb custom_facts processes the native custom facts from Ansible facts.d format? 

The JSON output from '/etc/ansible/facts.d/custom_facts.fact' on host1 in my example is like this: 

`         "ansible_local": {
            "custom_facts": {
                "services": {
                    "apache": {
                        "install_src": "backport_deb", 
                        "version": "2.4"
                    }, 
                    "mysql-server": {
                        "install_src": "manual_compile", 
                        "version": "5.5"
                    }, 
                    "redis": {
                        "install_src": "manual_compile", 
                        "version": "3.0.7"
                    }
                }
            }
        }`

,where I want to process the facts under 'services'. But, Ansible adds the 'ansible_local' key. 

This is not an 'issue' - just a question / request on how I might be able to use ansible custom_facts in a dynamic way with CMDB.

Thanks!

